<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-03-04T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-03-04T07:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                            <head>189. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in
                                    Israel</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                    State</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d189fn1">Source:
                                    Department of State, Central Files, 674.84A/3–457. Confidential;
                                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>. Received at 7:28
                                    a.m.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="italic">Tel
                                            Aviv</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-03-04T14:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">March 4,
                                            1957—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>1022. Foreign Ministry official telephoned Embassy at 1:00 p.m. local
                                time to say <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben Gurion</persName> has
                                decided to withdraw, and <persName corresp="#p_DMGM1">Dayan</persName> has been instructed meet <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName> earliest opportunity to
                                discuss details. He has already cabled <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName> asking for meeting.</p>
                            <p>Official added that while decision will be announced this afternoon,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben Gurion</persName>’s address to
                                Knesset, earlier scheduled for today, has been postponed until
                                tomorrow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_LEB1"><hi rend="strong">Lawson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>